are basically overnight unsecured lending to the bank which is why they=E2=
=80=99re near 0%; 2) Liquidity trap from years of low interest rates. Borro=
wers are not borrowing not because they don=E2=80=99t want to but because t=
hey already are saddled with debt. Corp debt is high, consumer debt is high=
=2E There is just no more room to borrow more.

